                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#4r">Fol. 4r</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol.4r: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘማርያም፡ መካን፡ ዕቁባ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለማርያም፡ መካን፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ አቡሁ፡ ወእሙ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ጻድቅ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወሀሙሁ፡ ገብረ፡ መድን፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወእኅቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ በዘመነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወጳጳስነ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"> Fol. 4r: This is a book of Maryam Mäkan, ʿƎquba Maryam, who has given it to Maryam Mäkan, and (of) his wife Wälättä Ḥǝywät, (of) his father and his mother, ʾabunä Gäbrä Ṣadǝq (and) Wälättä Ḥǝywät, and his wife Wälättä Ḥǝywät, and his father-in-law Gäbrä Mädǝn, and his wife Wälättä Haymanot, and his sister Wälättä Giyorgis. In the year of John, (under) our king Ḫaylä Śǝllase and our bishop Marqos, so that it might be for him a guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. He who stole it or erased (its text) shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul.</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#160r">Fol. 160r</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 160r: ፲፱፻፴፭ዓመት፡ ዕቁባ፡ ማርያም፡ ገብረ፡ ጻድቅ፡ በ፸፪{ብ፡} ገዝቶ፡ ለእንዳ፡ {ማርያ፡} መካኖ [sic]፡ ሰጥቷል፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 160r: The year 1935, ʿƎquba Maryam Gäbrä Ṣadǝq has bought (it) for 72 Bǝrr and given to ʾƎnda Marya(m) Mäkano.</q>
                           The note is written in Amharic. The year 1935 (of mercy) corresponds to 1941/42 A.D. Beneath the note, a passage in Gǝʿǝz is added, in pink ink: ምስለ፡ አመታ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሩ፡ ገብረ፡ መድኅን፡
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Traces of red paint or ink on the folio: fols. 1r, 160v.&#xD;
- The hymn Śärawitä mälaʾǝktihu lä-mädḫane ʿaläm... „The hosts of the angels of the Saviour of the world...“ is written in smaller script in the upper or bottom margin: fols. 103r, 128r.&#xD;
- Short crude note, in the upper margin: fol. 123r.</item>
